Class NormalizingFeatureProcessor

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, IFeatureProcessor<double[]>

    public class NormalizingFeatureProcessor
extends AbstractVectorMappingFeatureProcessor
    Enables the normalization and mean removal of features. Normalization can be done on the range of values or the standard deviation. Normalization and mean removal can be done on the full matrix of features, on individual feature vectors, or across time. Range normalization and mean remove will produce results in the range [-0.5, 0.5].
    Author:
    dawood

      • NormalizingFeatureProcessor

        public NormalizingFeatureProcessor(boolean normalizeStddev,
                                   boolean zeroMean,
                                   boolean acrossFeature,
                                   boolean acrossTime)
        Normalize the feature for standard deviation or value range, and/or adjustment to a zero mean. Normalization may be done across one of 3 target components
        1. the whole matrix/spectrogram of features
        2. the feature values for a each time slot in the matrix (i.e. each column of the feature matrix).
        3. each feature coefficient across time (i.e. each row of the feature matrix).
        Parameters:
        normalizeStddev - if true, then normalize the standard deviation in the target component, otherwise normalize using the range of values in the target component.
        zeroMean - if true, then set the mean of the target component to 0.
        acrossFeature - if true, then normalize the feature within a time slot. If this is true and acrossTime is true, then normalize across the whole matrix/spectrogram.
        acrossTime - if true, then normalize the features across time. If this is true and acrossFeature is true, then normalize across the whole matrix/spectrogram. if both are false, then no normalization is done.

        Description copied from class: AbstractVectorMappingFeatureProcessor
        Map the given array of double arrays to a new array of double arrays. The number of double arrays returned need not be the same as in the input, and the length of each double array can be different than the input.
        Specified by:
        map in class AbstractVectorMappingFeatureProcessor
        Parameters:
        features - The original features from which the data is extracted.
        featureData - the data extracted from the given features. Should NOT be modified.
        Returns:
        never null. May return the given featureData array in which case the features are not modified. May return a 0x0 matrix (new double[0][]) if the matrix of features could not be created (e.g., not enough data, etc).
